  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Wolfsberg Principles\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Financial institution screening\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal penalties\n- Financial sanctions\n- Asset seizure\n- Prosecution of individuals and organizations\n\n5. Global Cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- International law enforcement collaboration\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different sectors and jurisdictions.",
